80 grams Green Beans
240 grams British Beef Mince
250 grams Riced Cauliflower
120 grams Coleslaw Mix
1 sachet(s) Indonesian Style Spice Mix
50 grams Ketjap Manis
15 milliliter(s) Rice Vinegar
15 grams Honey
25 milliliter(s) Soy Sauce
25 grams Salted Peanuts
50 milliliter(s) Water for the Sauce

Boil a half-full kettle. Trim and halve the green beans.
While the kettle boils, heat a drizzle of oil in a frying pan on high heat.
Once hot, fry the beef mince and beans, 5-6 mins.
Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with salt and pepper. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Heat a medium frying pan on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.
Once hot, add the riced cauliflower.
Cook until just soft, 3-4 mins. Season with salt and pepper.
Once cooked, cover to keep warm until serving.

Next, add the coleslaw mix to the veg.
Stir the Indonesian style spice mix, ketjap manis, rice vinegar, honey, soy and water (see pantry) into the mince. TIP: Pop hardened honey into hot water for 1 min.
Simmer, 3-4 mins.
Add a splash of water to the beef if needed. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Remove from the heat.

Share the cauli rice and stir-fry between your bowls.
Sprinkle over the peanuts.
Enjoy!